(MAN SPEAKING ON MICROPHONE)

35
00:06:14.500 --> 00:06:18.879
(MELODICALLY) <i>Two snake that you see,
they are Siamese cobra or common cobra.</i>

36
00:06:20.172 --> 00:06:23.801
<i>He is not king cobra and not spitting cobra.</i>

37
00:06:25.177 --> 00:06:26.971
(HISSING)

38
00:06:35.813 --> 00:06:36.939
Hey! Hey!

39
00:06:37.022 --> 00:06:38.649
(SPEAKING THAI)

40
00:06:47.116 --> 00:06:48.158
Fuck off, okay?

41
00:06:51.161 --> 00:06:53.330
(MAN SPEAKING ON MICROPHONE)

42
00:06:54.248 --> 00:06:57.501
<i>They still have fang and still have poison.</i>

43
00:06:59.295 --> 00:07:01.589
<i>He is small, dangerous, number one.</i>

44
00:07:01.672 --> 00:07:02.756
(INAUDIBLE)

45
00:07:02.840 --> 00:07:05.009
<i>King cobra number two.</i>

46
00:07:06.260 --> 00:07:08.095
<i>And now spitting cobra.</i>

47
00:07:08.178 --> 00:07:10.764
<i>He can spit poison to your eye.</i>

48
00:07:13.350 --> 00:07:14.685
<i>One color.</i>

49
00:07:16.186 --> 00:07:19.565
<i>He’s very, very dangerous.
Number one in Thailand.</i>

50
00:07:20.482 --> 00:07:21.692
<i>Careful, my friend.</i>

51
00:07:23.777 --> 00:07:25.070
Looks like dangerous work.

52
00:07:28.073 --> 00:07:30.409
I'm Michael Burnett.
Do you have some time to talk?

53
00:07:31.327 --> 00:07:33.037
Won't take long, I promise.

54
00:07:33.287 --> 00:07:35.456
I was told it might be possible
to rent your boat.

55
00:07:35.539 --> 00:07:36.540
We'd like to do that.

56
00:07:36.915 --> 00:07:39.126
Is that possible? We need to get upriver.

57
00:07:39.209 --> 00:07:41.545
-Where you going?
-Into Burma.

58
00:07:42.838 --> 00:07:44.089
Burma's a war zone.

59
00:07:44.173 --> 00:07:48.469
Well, that's what people call it,
but it's more like genocide than war.

60
00:07:49.511 --> 00:07:54.266
Anyway, this will be my fifth trip in,
so we are aware of all the risks.

61
00:07:57.436 --> 00:07:58.896
I don't go that far north.

62
00:07:59.897 --> 00:08:01.523
Let me explain our situation.

63
00:08:01.607 --> 00:08:05.611
Our church is part of a Pan-Asian ministry
located in Colorado,

64
00:08:05.694 --> 00:08:08.739
and we're all volunteers
who around this time of year

65
00:08:08.822 --> 00:08:12.451
bring in medical supplies,
medical attention,

66
00:08:12.534 --> 00:08:15.496
prayer books and support
for the Karen tribes people.

67
00:08:16.705 --> 00:08:19.083
People say
you know the river better than anyone.

68
00:08:19.166 --> 00:08:20.167
Well, they lied.

69
00:08:20.250 --> 00:08:23.045
So, what I'm asking is that
we compensate you

70
00:08:23.128 --> 00:08:25.506
for a few hours of your time.

71
00:08:25.589 --> 00:08:27.591
It will help change people's lives.

72
00:08:31.345 --> 00:08:33.889
-Are you bringing in any weapons?
-Of course not.

73
00:08:34.431 --> 00:08:36.100
You're not changing anything.

74
00:08:37.768 --> 00:08:38.977
Well...

75
00:08:40.604 --> 00:08:43.857
It's thinking like that
that keeps the world the way it is.

76
00:08:43.941 --> 00:08:45.275
Fuck the world.

77
00:08:48.529 --> 00:08:50.030
-Let's go.
-Why?

78
00:08:50.114 --> 00:08:52.199
He's not interested. Let's just go.

79
00:08:52.282 --> 00:08:53.617
-Let me try.
-No, Sarah...

80
00:08:53.701 --> 00:08:55.119
No, didn't you say
it was the only way up there?

81
00:08:55.202 --> 00:08:56.995
-I know I did...
-All right, then what do we have to lose?

82
00:08:57.079 --> 00:08:58.372
-I talked to the man...
-Just let me try, Michael.

83
00:08:58.455 --> 00:08:59.623
-Sarah...
-Please.

84
00:09:14.471 --> 00:09:15.639
Hello?

85
00:09:17.182 --> 00:09:18.642
I'm Sarah Miller.

86
00:09:19.893 --> 00:09:22.229
I hope you don't mind me
coming back here.

87
00:09:24.523 --> 00:09:26.316
The man that you were talking to...

88
00:09:26.400 --> 00:09:28.068
I wasn't talking to anybody.

89
00:09:30.654 --> 00:09:31.905
All right.

90
00:09:31.989 --> 00:09:33.449
The man that was talking to you

91
00:09:33.532 --> 00:09:36.827
asked if we could hire you
to take us up the river.

92
00:09:37.161 --> 00:09:39.997
-You said no. Why?
-Can't help you out.

93
00:09:42.708 --> 00:09:45.085
Well, if you have good reasons,
would you mind if I heard them?

94
00:09:48.714 --> 00:09:50.007
Go home.

95
00:10:09.485 --> 00:10:11.361
(MEN SHOUTING)

96
00:10:11.445 --> 00:10:12.863
(CLAMORING)

97
00:10:33.717 --> 00:10:35.177
(CLAMORING)

98
00:10:48.106 --> 00:10:50.150
(SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

99
00:11:20.764 --> 00:11:22.266
(SHOUTING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

100
00:11:23.767 --> 00:11:25.269
(SCREAMING)

101
00:11:55.465 --> 00:11:57.009
You shouldn't be in here.

102
00:11:57.885 --> 00:11:59.386
Would you reconsider?

103
00:12:02.055 --> 00:12:05.058
Look, I don't know anything about you,

104
00:12:05.809 --> 00:12:08.729
and it seems like you don't care to know
anything about us.

105
00:12:08.812 --> 00:12:09.855
Sarah.

106
00:12:09.938 --> 00:12:13.191
But you live so close
to what's going on over here.

107
00:12:15.319 --> 00:12:17.195
I mean, doesn't it bother you at all?

108
00:12:17.571 --> 00:12:18.655
It's not my business.

109
00:12:19.031 --> 00:12:20.449
Sarah, we should go.

110
00:12:20.991 --> 00:12:22.701
(HAMMERING)

111
00:12:28.498 --> 00:12:32.336
Do you believe that people are put here
to die for no reason?

112
00:12:36.840 --> 00:12:38.926
Or believe in giving time to something
other than yourself?

113
00:12:39.009 --> 00:12:40.594
I mean, do you believe in anything?

114
00:12:48.644 --> 00:12:49.770
You really ought to go.

115
00:12:57.861 --> 00:13:01.114
The man doesn't care.
We'll figure something out.

116
00:13:15.337 --> 00:13:16.880
(ALL CLAMORING)

117
00:13:19.007 --> 00:13:20.342
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

118
00:13:40.737 --> 00:13:42.072
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

119
00:13:45.659 --> 00:13:47.077
(SCREAMING)

120
00:13:57.546 --> 00:14:00.048
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

121
00:14:02.759 --> 00:14:04.094
(WAILING)

122
00:15:33.016 --> 00:15:34.267
Why'd you come back?

123
00:15:36.645 --> 00:15:37.896
Waiting for you.

124
00:15:40.065 --> 00:15:42.275
-I told you before, I can't help you.
-Why?

125
00:15:43.944 --> 00:15:45.028
I don't want to.

126
00:15:50.033 --> 00:15:52.953
-Where are your friends?
-At the hotel.

127
00:15:53.245 --> 00:15:54.663
I can take care of myself.

128
00:15:55.288 --> 00:15:57.040
-Is that so?
-Yes.

129
00:15:57.874 --> 00:15:59.709
-I know you don't like us.
-I never said that.

130
00:15:59.793 --> 00:16:00.961
Well, it looks that way.

131
00:16:03.213 --> 00:16:04.923
We need to go and help these people.

132
00:16:05.382 --> 00:16:06.508
Who are you helping?

133
00:16:08.593 --> 00:16:09.845
Them or you?

134
00:16:09.928 --> 00:16:11.763
-Does it matter?
-Yeah, it matters.

135
00:16:12.305 --> 00:16:13.390
Them.

136
00:16:13.473 --> 00:16:15.892
There's nothing missing
in our lives back home.

137
00:16:15.976 --> 00:16:17.227
We're here to make a difference.

138
00:16:17.853 --> 00:16:19.813
We believe all lives are special.

139
00:16:19.896 --> 00:16:21.898
-Some lives, some, no.
-Really?

140
00:16:22.190 --> 00:16:24.234
If everyone thought like you,
nothing would ever change.

141
00:16:24.317 --> 00:16:25.318
Nothing does change.

142
00:16:25.402 --> 00:16:27.654
Of course it does. Nothing stays the same.

143
00:16:27.904 --> 00:16:29.614
Live your life, 'cause you got a good one.

144
00:16:29.698 --> 00:16:31.158
It's what I'm trying to do.

145
00:16:31.241 --> 00:16:33.326
No, what you're trying to do
is change what is.

146
00:16:33.410 --> 00:16:35.328
-And what is?
-That we're like animals.

147
00:16:37.455 --> 00:16:40.083
It's in the blood. It's natural.

148
00:16:41.126 --> 00:16:42.544
Peace, that's an accident.

149
00:16:43.628 --> 00:16:44.796
It's what is.

150
00:16:46.089 --> 00:16:50.510
When you're pushed,
killing is as easy as breathing.

151
00:16:53.430 --> 00:16:56.016
Then the killing stops in one place
and it starts in another,

152
00:16:56.099 --> 00:16:59.519
but that's okay
'cause you're killing for your country.

153
00:17:00.437 --> 00:17:04.107
But it ain't your country who's asking.
It's a few men up top who want it.

154
00:17:05.275 --> 00:17:08.153
Old men start it, young men fight it.

155
00:17:08.695 --> 00:17:11.948
Nobody wins, everybody in the middle dies.

156
00:17:13.617 --> 00:17:15.118
And nobody tells the truth.

157
00:17:16.828 --> 00:17:18.580
God's gonna make all that go away?

158
00:17:34.054 --> 00:17:37.182
Don't waste your life. I did.

159
00:17:41.895 --> 00:17:43.146
Go home.

160
00:17:46.358 --> 00:17:47.651
Really. Go home.

161
00:18:06.461 --> 00:18:08.380
-You care.
-What?

162
00:18:09.881 --> 00:18:10.882
You care.

163
00:18:12.676 --> 00:18:16.346
Because if you didn't,
you would have taken us there,

164
00:18:16.972 --> 00:18:19.599
taken the money and be done with it.

165
00:18:21.685 --> 00:18:23.019
But you didn't do that.

166
00:18:36.074 --> 00:18:37.575
Maybe...

167
00:18:37.659 --> 00:18:39.953
Maybe you've lost your faith in people,

168
00:18:41.371 --> 00:18:43.707
but you must still be faithful to something.

169
00:18:47.294 --> 00:18:50.338
Believe me, I'm scared.

170
00:18:51.881 --> 00:18:55.135
And I love my life
and I don't want to lose it.

171
00:18:57.554 --> 00:19:02.309
But trying to save a life
isn't wasting your life, is it?

172
00:19:07.564 --> 00:19:08.648
Will you help us?

173
00:19:18.742 --> 00:19:19.909
All right.

174
00:19:23.330 --> 00:19:24.331
Thank you.

175
00:19:41.931 --> 00:19:44.601
BURNETT: As bad as these people are,
they will eventually lose.

176
00:19:45.101 --> 00:19:47.896
They can't keep it up against a united front.
They can't.

177
00:19:48.772 --> 00:19:51.524
I mean, time alone will tell,
but in the meantime,

178
00:19:51.608 --> 00:19:53.234
we just have to help hold it together.

179
00:19:54.027 --> 00:19:55.779
I mean, just the other day, I read...

180
00:19:56.029 --> 00:19:57.030
Excuse me.

181
00:19:57.113 --> 00:19:59.115
Sarah, where are you going?

182
00:20:00.075 --> 00:20:01.659
To talk to him.

183
00:20:01.743 --> 00:20:03.620
Well, he probably wants his privacy.

184
00:20:03.703 --> 00:20:05.121
Michael, you shouldn't ignore him.

185
00:20:05.205 --> 00:20:07.290
-He's helping us.
-He's been paid.

186
00:20:07.791 --> 00:20:09.125
He didn't take anything.

187
00:20:16.925 --> 00:20:20.929
Thank you, again, for doing this.
Really. From all of us.

188
00:20:26.976 --> 00:20:29.229
It's like the same view goes on forever.

189
00:20:29.813 --> 00:20:31.147
It's so empty out here.

190
00:20:32.315 --> 00:20:33.608
It just looks that way.

191
00:20:36.194 --> 00:20:38.154
You know, you never told us your name.

192
00:20:39.489 --> 00:20:40.824
-John.
-John.

193
00:20:42.492 --> 00:20:44.619
-Lived here a long time?
-Long time.

194
00:20:47.122 --> 00:20:51.000
-Where you from?
-Bowie, Arizona. Small place.

195
00:20:53.002 --> 00:20:54.003
What'd you do there?

196
00:20:56.589 --> 00:20:57.841
Worked horses, mainly.

197
00:20:58.633 --> 00:21:01.511
-Why'd you leave?
-I got drafted in Nam.

198
00:21:03.179 --> 00:21:07.684
-Long time ago.
-Long time ago. Lot of years.

199
00:21:08.143 --> 00:21:09.436
And you just stayed?

200
00:21:11.312 --> 00:21:12.689
It's complicated.

201
00:21:13.648 --> 00:21:17.235
-You have family back home?
-Father maybe. I don't know.

202
00:21:20.321 --> 00:21:23.283
Aren't you curious to see
how things might've changed back home?

203
00:21:25.869 --> 00:21:27.537
Got to have a reason for that.

204
00:21:37.547 --> 00:21:41.885
-What do you do stateside?
-I teach. Sixth grade.

205
00:21:44.554 --> 00:21:45.805
What?

206
00:21:45.889 --> 00:21:47.807
Now I know why you ask
so many questions.

207
00:21:57.025 --> 00:22:00.069
-Any idea how much longer?
-Yeah, just a few more hours.

208
00:22:02.405 --> 00:22:04.032
Maybe we should give the man his space.

209
00:22:07.202 --> 00:22:09.746
We should go over the schedule, okay?

210
00:22:10.788 --> 00:22:11.789
Okay.

211
00:22:18.755 --> 00:22:22.091
We're engaged. He's a good man.

212
00:22:23.593 --> 00:22:24.594
That's good.

213
00:22:26.346 --> 00:22:30.433
I know you think you live alone out here,
but there's always something pushing you.

214
00:23:29.617 --> 00:23:32.078
-What is it? Who are they?
-Burmese pirates.

215
00:23:32.996 --> 00:23:34.622
Tell everyone to stay down,
don't make a sound.

216
00:23:36.791 --> 00:23:38.668
-Who are they?
-It's all right, it's all right.

217
00:23:38.751 --> 00:23:39.877
-Just keep...
-Don't talk!

218
00:24:20.418 --> 00:24:22.211
-Any more of them?
-Maybe.

219
00:24:22.462 --> 00:24:23.671
What do you wanna do?

220
00:24:24.047 --> 00:24:26.049
We should keep going.
We made a commitment.

221
00:24:26.299 --> 00:24:27.717
-What do you wanna do?
-We're a group here.

222
00:24:27.800 --> 00:24:28.926
If they wanna vote...

223
00:24:29.177 --> 00:24:30.553
(RUMBLING)

224
00:24:31.512 --> 00:24:33.431
-Sit down!
-If it's money they want...

225
00:24:37.352 --> 00:24:39.562
Nobody talks. Heads down.

226
00:24:48.404 --> 00:24:50.198
Keep your heads down
and nobody look them in the eye,

227
00:24:50.281 --> 00:24:51.282
or they'll kill you.

228
00:25:09.926 --> 00:25:11.302
(WHIMPERS)

229
00:25:12.428 --> 00:25:15.139
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

230
00:26:32.383 --> 00:26:33.634
(GASPS)

231
00:26:42.935 --> 00:26:43.936
No!

232
00:26:51.444 --> 00:26:52.695
BURNETT: What did you do?

233
00:26:53.529 --> 00:26:55.239
We came here to help stop the killing!

234
00:26:55.323 --> 00:26:57.700
-Who are you to...
-Who are you?

235
00:26:57.784 --> 00:26:59.118
-(CHOKING)
-Let him go!

236
00:26:59.202 --> 00:27:02.914
They would've raped her 50 times,
and cut your heads off.

237
00:27:03.664 --> 00:27:04.999
We're going back!

238
00:27:10.046 --> 00:27:12.632
No. No, we shouldn't go back.

239
00:27:12.715 --> 00:27:14.675
-What are you doing?
-Don't take us back.

240
00:27:14.759 --> 00:27:16.469
-Look what just happened!
-We got through it.

241
00:27:16.552 --> 00:27:19.430
-We'II come back next year.
-We are so close.

242
00:27:19.722 --> 00:27:24.477
Michael, this was your idea.
We made a commitment.

243
00:27:25.728 --> 00:27:28.481
I know you don't believe
in what we're doing,

244
00:27:28.564 --> 00:27:31.067
but it's our life, our choice.

245
00:27:34.904 --> 00:27:38.157
Please. Please, John.

246
00:27:38.574 --> 00:27:39.784
